CHAT.comment: First home visit; took place in dining room , CHI seated in her own chair next to that of the Mot; played with toys on the dining room table

INV2 had been playing with CHI while INV1 conducted the interview and she was talking quite a bit; both researchers think that she is frightened of INV1 who sits nearest her; INV2 talks on this tape more than in a normal home visit in an attempt at getting CHI to feel comfortable

u.a: INV1 and pour toys out on the dining room table; CHI helps minimally
everyone starts to take toys out of the bag
CHI and Mot put the people on the bus
CHI drops a toy on the table
CHI goes to her room to get one of her dolls
CHI comes back and begins to feed the baby doll
goes to her bedroom to get her teapot
comes back in with her teapot
very high pitched whistle follows previous utterance
pretends to pour her mother coffee
high-pitched whistle overlaps all of previous two utterances
cuddles up to her Mother , acts very babyish and does not say anything
doesn't want to use that bowl and goes to her room to get her own bowl
puts the alphabet soup in a bowl
high pitched whistle again follows previous utterance , overlaps next utterance
the phone rings in the kitchen and Mot goes to answer it
Dwinette pretends to dial , makes a ringing sound and waits for CHI to pick up her phone; Mot has finished talking on the phone and walks back in the dining room
INV2 , INV1 and MOt are all encouraged by the reaction; she is opening up again
